# MoneyTracker — Privacy Policy

This is a single-user, personal-use application running locally on the operator's own hardware. The operator is the only data subject.

## Data accessed

- Bank account information (accounts, balances, transactions) via Enable Banking, Monzo Developer API, and eToro Public API — all accessed read-only, under the operator's own consent.
- Optional: transaction descriptions may be sent to Anthropic (Claude API) for categorization assistance.

## Read-only mandate

This application **never** writes to any bank or broker API. It cannot move money, place trades, post payments, or change any external state. Code-side enforcement gates every commit against forbidden write endpoints; provider-side enforcement uses minimum read scopes and (where available) IP whitelisting.

## Data storage

- All financial data is stored in a local PostgreSQL database on the operator's own machine.
- No cloud database, no third-party hosting, no shared infrastructure.

## Data sharing

- No data is shared with third parties.
- No analytics, advertising, or tracking.
- No marketing communications.
- The only outbound network egress is to the APIs listed above (Enable Banking, Monzo, eToro, Anthropic).

## Data retention

- Data is retained for as long as the operator chooses. The operator can delete it at any time.
- The operator can revoke any provider's access at any time via that provider's app/portal.

